org.finra.herd.dao

Class ReloadablePropertySource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.core.env.PropertySource<T>
      • org.springframework.core.env.EnumerablePropertySource<Map<String,Object>>
        • org.springframework.core.env.MapPropertySource
          • org.finra.herd.dao.ReloadablePropertySource

  • public class ReloadablePropertySource
extends org.springframework.core.env.MapPropertySource
    A property source that will possibly re-load itself each time a property is requested. A reload will take place if the configured refresh interval has elapsed. A refresh interval of 0 will cause the properties to refresh every time a property is requested.

    If a property is loaded with the key org.finra.herd.dao.ReloadablePropertiesSource.refreshIntervalSecs, it will be used as a way to override the previously configured refresh interval.
